description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are a highly motivated, proactive, forward thinking Nurse Practitioner then you could be just the person we are looking for.  East Lynne Medical Centre has an opening for a qualified and innovative ANP to join our progressive practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will play a vital role in the development and delivery of a sustainable and patient centred service.  You will act as an autonomous practitioner working independently and collaboratively with other health care professionals to assess, diagnose and treat the conditions of patients within primary care, initiating direct referrals as appropriate.   You will also be responsible for developing new and innovative concepts, models, methods and practices to deliver new and improved primary care services to meet the needs of our patient population.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role has the potential to significantly improve quality of care and safety for our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please see the attached job spec for full details.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you like what you have read and feel you are the person we are seeking, please apply.  We would be happy to have a conversation with you prior to application and you are welcome to come and visit East Lynne Medical Centre (social distancing observed).  Please contact Melinda Gooding on 01255 220010 or by email Melinda.gooding1@nhs.net who will be happy to arrange this for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The closing date for completed applications is Thursday 5th November 2020.    &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Candidate&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;The post holder will be an experienced clinician, a Nurse Practitioner or Paramedic with an IP qualification (V300) or already on the IP course who, acting within their professional boundaries to provide clinical assessment and management of patients About Us:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting time to join East Lynne Medical Centre, we are on a journey to excellence and are striving to improve healthcare for all our patients.  We are a team of multi-disciplinary highly skilled health care professionals who are passionate about what we do and are driving innovation to improve our patients experience and outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is also being advertised on the Essex Primary Care Careers website – please complete only one application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have the right to close the advert earlier if we reach the maximum number of applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NO AGENCIES PLEASE&lt;/p&gt;
